net.dnddev.factions.store

Class LoadFaction

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dnddev.factions.store.LoadFaction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Faction, Messageable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MongoFaction

    public abstract class LoadFaction
extends Object
implements Faction
    The in-memory representation of a Faction.

    To help reduce clutter and duplicate code, Factions have an additional middle step between the interface and the implementation that saves to the database.

    This should only ever be used if you are making major changes to Factions. Many checks and a lot of logic is done within this class, so be careful with what exactly is touched. When in doubt, reference the original source code.

    Author:
    Michael Ziluck

      • getMembers

        public List<User> getMembers()
        Description copied from interface: Faction
        Retrieves all the members of the Faction. This includes the leader.

        This method is lazy loading by default, meaning that it will only load the members when it is called for the first time rather than when it is started. This ensures that unnecessary memory is not used up to ensure it is as efficient as possible. This feature can be turned off in the config, but it is advisable to be left on.
        Specified by:
        getMembers in interface Faction
        Returns:
        all members of the Faction.
